    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA35-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu maṇamaṉaip piṟṟaiñāṉṟu pukka tōḻi “naṉku āṟṟuvittāy” eṉṟa talaimakaṟkuc colliyatu (EV: tōḻiyait talaivaṉ “naṉku āṟṟuvittāy” eṉṟataṟku avaḷ colliyatu).</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante who had entered the marriage house some time after said to HIM: “you have kept up well!” (EV: This is what the confidante said to HIM who had said to her “you have kept up well”.)</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA35">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            poṅkutirai poruta vārmaṇa laṭaikaraip</l>
<l>            puṉkā ṉāvaṟ potippuṟa viruṅkaṉi</l>
<l>            kiḷaicettu moytta tumpi paḻañcettup</l>
<l>            palkā lalavaṉ koṇṭakōṭ kūrntu</l>
<l>            koḷḷā narampi ṉimirum pūca </l>
<l>            liraitēr nārai yeyti viṭukkun</l>
<l>            tuṟaikeḻu māntai yaṉṉa vivaṇalam</l>
<l>            paṇṭu miṟṟē kaṇṭiciṟ ṟeyya</l>
<l>            vuḻaiyiṟ pōkā taḷippiṉuñ ciṟiya</l>
<l>            ñekiḻnta kaviṉalaṅ kollō makiḻntōr </l>
<l>            kaṭkaḻi cerukkat taṉṉa</l>
<l>            kāmaṅ kollivaḷ kaṇpacan tatuvē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Just see! [Was] like this ever before</l>
<l>her beauty,</l>
<l rend="indent3">like Māntai with [its] ghat,</l>
<l rend="indent3">where the prey-searching heron gets [and] lets go,</l>
<l rend="indent3">after proceeding for the catch that took the many-legged crab </l>
<l rend="indent">[because of?] the clamour,</l>
<l rend="indent">when the bee sounds like a [lute] string that is played, thinking of fruit, </l>
<l rend="indent">[the bee] that swarmed, thinking of [its] relations<note place="foot">Here the point might be that the bee, which has found a promising site, swarms back to inform its fellow bees of the good fortune (as bees actually do).</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the dark ripe fruits with stout backs on the low-trunked Nāval tree,</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the shore where sand settles, overflown when hit by foaming waves.</l>
<l rend="indent">Even if [he] provides [for her] without going out of [her] presence,</l>
<l>[is this her] beautiful appearance, slightly<note place="foot">Has <term xml:lang="ta">ciṟiya</term> to be taken adverbially or does it refer to something on HER, such as her "small [bangles]", which would go well with <term xml:lang="foot">ñekiḻnta</term>, the usual word for bangles coming loose?</note> emaciated?</l>
<l rend="indent">Like the passing intoxication by toddy in those who are delighted [by it],</l>
<l>[is this] desire? Her eye has become pale.<note place="foot">For parallels of attributing the pallor rather to her eyes than to her forehead</note></l>
        </lg>
